<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The City of High Elves – Felwithe</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Travelers’ Inn</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The High Priest of Tunare Jeez met the proprietors of the Traveler’s Inn with a generous smile and a nod of his head. His good mood was expressed in his shining, green eyes; the rosy glow in his fair skin; and the spring in his every step. It was in his voice as he paused to chat the inn’s proprietors and a the guests that happened to wander past, making pleasant small-talk before offering them his goddess’ blessings and moving on in the same fashion he had greeted them.<br>
<br>
Jeez quickly ascended the carpeted staircase and walked casually down a short hall. The inn was a quaint affair, by Koada’Dall standards. Not so grand that it was impersonal, and not so small that it seemed haunted by quiet. It was intimate with the understated elegance that served his personal tastes. His fondness for the establishment made him one its favored patrons. Hardly a day passed that one of its many rooms was not occupied by one of the cleric’s visiting friends.<br>
<br>
His current thought was on one such friend as he came upon the door to the inn’s finest room. He rapped lightly on the door.<br>
<br>
“Come in.”<br>
<br>
Her voice fell over his ears with the softness of feathers, though Jeez could hear an unaccustomed edge in its tone even now. He opened the door and gracefully stepped inside.<br>
<br>
She stood behind a dressing screen that was decorated with a scene of cherry tree in full blossom and the rain of its soft pink petals. The thin fabric upon which the work was rendered caught the room’s light and the guest’s shadow. Jeez eyed the curves of her silhouette and the grace in its motion as if hypnotized.<br>
<br>
“You were too kind, Jeez, to go through all the trouble of arranging this room on such short notice.” She said from behind the screen.<br>
<br>
“Nonsense. I would do anything in my power...”<br>
<br>
His words died away as Candra stepped into view. She wore an elegant, black gown he’d never seen before, with matching gloves that rose just below her elbows. Not overly formal, Jeez thought. He reasoned that she needed only finely crafted simplicity to compliment a radiant beauty that would outshine any accoutrements.<br>
<br>
“My goddess, you are ravishing,” he found himself saying. Candra smiled demurely with a subtle batting of eyelashes. Jeez basked in the obvious danger of her appeal. Her considerable beauty was both more and less than it seemed: more than mere physical perfection; less than completely candid. Her mystique was the crux of her powers. This Jeez well knew. Yet the stirrings of sentiment that her mere presence aroused in him were intoxicating. Passions moved that he had not felt in...well, ever. He moved closer, like a moth circling an open flame.<br>
<br>
“I doubt I’ll ever be able to repay you for all your kindness.” She said.<br>
<br>
He slipped around her, but then paused. There it was again, that slight tension in he voice that he did not remember from previous encounters.<br>
<br>
“The chance to feast on you in the sight of this dress,” he said, grinning wolfishly. “...is more than payment enough, my love.”<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>My love</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, he repeated in his mind. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>How I indulge myself</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Only because he was attuned to the mysterious strain in Candra’s voice did he notice the muscles of her bare shoulders tense slightly at the word payment.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>She has debts outstanding that must be paid.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Jeez speculated. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Perhaps I can be of assistance? Perhaps I can find a way to bind her to me. But the cleric paused for only a brief moment</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
“I have taken the liberty...” he began as he produced two platinum earrings, intricately engraved. The metal was mundane, but the design was breath-taking. He reached around Candra and placed them in her hand. “Would you do me the honor?”<br>
<br>
She turned a ruddy cheek toward him and smiled as she put them on.<br>
<br>
“And of course...” he continued, presenting her with a matching necklace and locket.<br>
<br>
“Jeez, you flatterer.”<br>
<br>
“I am too smitten with your beauty to offer you anything so disingenuous as flattery.” He lowered the locket over her head. The locket was flattened and bordered on being large. Like her gown, it was elegant in its simplicity of form, yet it bore the markings of the earrings. For many women the locket would have been to much; not so with Candra.<br>
<br>
Jeez lowered it against the hollow of her breasts as he fastened the clasp behind her neck. Candra’s skin radiated warmth. The cleric breathed in her luxurious fragrance. He had neither touched nor laid eyes on the necklace in many years. It had been in his family for centuries, which wasn’t such a long time considering the lifespan of elves. Still, it was a meaningful gift. He had the urge – the desire, the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>need</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> – to bring it tonight.<br>
<br>
As Candra turned to face him, Jeez breathed the sigh of a cleric who had long contemplated sacrilege and was relieved to have finally given in.<br>
<br>
She placed a slender hand on his cheek, “Jeez, it’s beautiful.”<br>
Jeez felt tears coming to his eyes. He leaned close and kissed her lightly on one cheek and then on the other. His lips burned with her fire.<br>
<br>
It was no coincidence that the inn was almost completely quiet. When Jeez had responded to Candra’s mental summons, he’d found her wrapped in robes that concealed her face and body completely. It was highly uncharacteristic behavior for the enchantress as he knew her. She’d not allowed him to look at her and she’d barely spoken to him. He’d heard the pain in her voice, the fear and when she’s refused to be taken to his home or the Temple of Tunare and implied that she needed a place to hide, he’d arranged this sanctuary for her. He took the liberty of arranging for the rental of most of the inn’s rooms to make sure Candra’s privacy was guaranteed.<br>
<br>
“Just a moment, Jeez, and I’ll be ready to go.” Candra stepped behind the wardrobe again, where she tended to some hidden possession. The slight tension in her voice was the only indication of her previous difficulties.<br>
<br>
Jeez knew Candra made her home in Katta Castelum, but couldn’t imagine what nightmare she’d just arrived from. And now, as he heard the locket click shut, and Candra rejoined him, he refused to broach the subject. He preferred simply to bathe in the nimbus of her glory. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=candraverbena>Candra Verbena</A> at: 5/7/03 8:12:11 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#AB8C5B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=candraverbena>Candra Verbena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(5/7/03 3:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~eden444/images/candra_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possession</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The City of Dark Elves - Neriak</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Third Gate, The L`Ogrim Estate</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Eiluned L'Ogrim stood quietly at the rear of the ritual chamber that currently served as conference hall. For the single, flickering candle that cast a wan light against the cloying, dark heat of the room the dark elf necromancer easily sorted out the forms of the other three bodies that kept her company. Not that she needed any light to assist at all. Like any other Teir`Dal, her eyes were attuned to darkness and her vision easily pierced the deepest shadows.<br>
<br>
An amused look was cast over her indigo expression and her crimson-laced lips bent into a sneer of a grin. The smell of fear in the air always put Eiluned in the best of moods, but when that scent was tinged with a sense of looming death she was ecstatic. It was all she could do to restrain herself from tittering like a young elf after her first kill.<br>
<br>
She stood away from the others. Her role in these dealings was an observer and witness.<br>
<br>
The Tier`Dal necromancer PuppetM stood at the heart of the chamber. The robe that dressed him was a black shell, a simple accessory to the shadows that clung to him like a second skin. He was looking down on two figures kneeling before him, fearful and reverent. The smaller figure was the Tier`Dal shadow knight and the PuppetM's's own son, Myurr. The other was a troll warrior whose simple name pointed out his most intriguing facet, Twocoloreyes. Neither had the courage to look up and face their master's dread gaze. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Very wise</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, Eiluned thought. She could see in her husband what so few could, heat and passion. She knew that both qualities had been pushed to their limit and any display of supposed strength from the two before him now would certainly push PuppetM a step beyond it. The outcome of such a thing would be...messy.<br>
<br>
&quot;You failed to capture the enchantress,&quot; PuppetM's voice was a cold thing, lacking in volume but powerful nonetheless. His expression held the same chill, inscrutable save for his blood red gaze. In them Eiluned observed the menace and bloodlust that won her attention first and then her affection later. She loved the monster she knew him to be. Among the body of Teir`Dal necromancers known as &quot;<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The Dead</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->&quot;, he was addressed as Warlock. It was a title earned through blood, sweat and death.<br>
<br>
Myurr did not look up as he addressed his father, &quot;We almost had the mind witch, father, but her tricks...&quot;<br>
<br>
PuppetM cut the other elf off, &quot;You failed.&quot;<br>
<br>
Eiluned hissed softly at Myurr, voicing her disapproval. It was the most she'd said so far. Her memory recalled the sight of Candra as she fled for her life. She had been ravaged by PuppetM's craft. The beauty that foolish men fell over themselves for had been peeled away to reveal the ugly thing Eiluned knew her to be; her flesh withered, that shapely form emaciated, and a generous flow of blood running from her thin, diseased lips. Eiluned smiled inwardly as she turned her attentions back to matters at hand.<br>
<br>
The junior of the L`Ogrim males went on, beads of sweat forming on his brow, &quot;We had her to rites, father and would have taken her, but at the last she managed some trick or charm that turned the tables...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You failed me,&quot; PuppetM repeated. &quot;I practically handed her to you, Myurr. She was weak and nearly depleted of her magical energies. You had only to move in for the kill. Instead you've returned to tell me that you and this worthless excuse for a servant that you dare call a warrior have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>failed me</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.&quot;<br>
<br>
A deep silence filled the room, making the already small space seem even more crowded. Eiluned could sense the dark power flowing from elf at the center of the room. Her limited understanding of the Art she shared with her husband could not make sense of the spell he was enacting. Her mind was reeling, her will being tested against the backlash of magic not even directed at her. She feared she could not stand in the face of such power; that she would show her weakness and faint. She braced against that feeling of claustrophobia and made a great effort to remain on her feet.<br>
<br>
Her eyes widened at the display of dark magic evoked at the heart of the room. Tendrils of thick shadows rose from the floor to ensnare Myurr and Twocoloreyes. She could make out the sounds of their armor being crushed, the slow crush of bones and their choked cries of pain and protest as the tendrils slithered tightly around their throats. Eiluned's own voice was lost to the awe of that display.<br>
<br>
&quot;What is it about you and failure, Myurr?&quot; PuppetM asked. It was a rhetorical question, of course. The warlock breathed a tried sigh as he walked a slow circle around the gasping, snapping, struggling duo. &quot;How is it that the enchantress managed to escape you?&quot;<br>
<br>
Myurr struggled with a reply. PuppetM acknowledged his son's effort with a subtle, dismissive gesture. With that the darkness retreated and dissipated. The troll landed to the floor in a wet, bleeding heap. Myurr landed on him and slowly rolled to the floor.<br>
<br>
Eiluned grinned as she watched the two struggle with their pain, gasping for breath and then choking on it. The troll vomited violently, blood bile and bits of dinner sprayed over the stone floor. Every twitch and spasm seemed to send a fresh, sharper wave of pain through. To his credit, Myurr showed amazing fortitude and managed to stand to his feet, though his ascent was slow and pained.<br>
<br>
PuppetM raised a brow inquiringly, &quot;Well? Out with it!&quot;<br>
<br>
Myurr spoke slowly as he described the pursuit through Nektulos Forest. He detailed a great battle against Candra's summoned protector and of her foiled efforts to open a gate to deliver her to safety. He recounted dismantling the animation and having his hand around her throat when a blow struck him from behind.<br>
<br>
PuppetM's expression soured further, &quot;This...Troll was your undoing?&quot; He darted a threatening look at Twocoloreyes. The warrior took a reflexive step backwards.<br>
<br>
&quot;He was charmed, father. Her powers were still great despite her injuries. She forced her will on Twocoloreyes, pitting him against me. As I raised my sword in defense...she escaped.&quot;<br>
<br>
Screaming terror seized the troll as PuppetM turned his full attention on him. Despite the fear that gripped him, Twocoloreyes could not run, he could not flee, and he could not raise a hand in his defense. The warlock's look alone held him in place. &quot;Such a weak mind is useless to me.&quot;<br>
<br>
PuppetM's features displayed a scornful look as he spat a curse at his victim. Darkness and disease put an end to the troll's life in the time it took for PuppetM to turn his red gaze back to Myurr. He spoke slowly, taking care to enunciate his words, &quot;Do not <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>fail me</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> again.&quot;<br>
<br>
PuppetM dismissed his son with a hard look. The younger elf responded with a display of reverence and humility, dropping to his knees before taking his leave.<br>
<br>
Eiluned allowed a full minute to pass before she peeled herself away from the wall that supported her back and joined her husband at the center of the room. She looked into his eyes and regarded him with an impish grin, &quot;Candra is more powerful than you care to admit. You made a good lesson of the troll, but perhaps you were a little too hard on Myurr.&quot;<br>
<br>
PuppetM stared back into Eiluned's cool, pale eyes, saying nothing.<br>
<br>
&quot;What is this bauble that she has taken from you?&quot; she inquired. Standing face to face with him, Eiluned realized that her husband wasn't looking at her all. His gaze looked through her. She could see the anger and desperation in his eyes. <br>
<br>
&quot;She will pay for her treachery.&quot; Without another word PuppetM turned away and left Eiluned alone to ponder the thin line between obsession and possession. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=candraverbena>Candra Verbena</A> at: 5/11/03 7:28:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#BA9F70><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=candraverbena>Candra Verbena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Regular</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(5/13/03 3:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~eden444/images/candra_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possession</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The City of High Elves - Felwithe<br>
