<br>
South Felwithe</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Candra took in the mountain of a man standing before her with an easy smile. His heart was beating faster than it should, making him ruddy and flushed. Beads of sweat wet the red moustache and the muttonchops that added to his barbarian flair and rough edges. She idly wondered if his excited state was the product of the liquor that she smelled on his breath, the thickening heat of the summer night, or the enchantment of adoring grace that always surrounded her. She made a guess that it was a combination of the three.<br>
<br>
Willius seemed satisfyingly surprised by her approach, although shock soon gave way to a wave of hungered emotions Candra took in with the pleasure of a gourmet sampling a new dish. &quot;Willius,&quot; she spoke his name the way he liked to hear it; soft and slow.<br>
<br>
The barbarian shaman responded with a hungry and boring grin of lust. His thoughts, in all likelihood never strayed beyond his most base desires. His only reaction was to shift his stance to shrug off his obvious discomfort. &quot;Good ta see ye again, lass. It's been some time.&quot;<br>
<br>
Candra's cherry lips parted in a smile meant to thrill. &quot;It's been only a day since we last spoke, Willius.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;A very long day,&quot; Willius replied. He peered about curiously then looked at Candra with a question &quot;And who is yer escort tonight? I doubt ya came alone.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Doubt? No, but you certainly hope</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. The enchantress kept that thought to herself, but did not try to conceal the mischief that brought it to mind. &quot;I arrived on Jeez's arm, but it seems Fayeth has stolen him away from my side to discuss matters of faith and devotion. Having no genuine interest in either quality and feeling the onset of a mild headache I excused myself to take a quiet stroll away from the solstice celebration.&quot;<br>
<br>
Willius grunted his assent. Candra could read the frustration in his expression. It wasn't so long ago that the barbarian standing before her gifted her with a ring and the promise of his eternal, unconditional love. Despite her deep affection and the powerful passion she felt for him, Candra decided against marrying Willius. The two remained good friends still. Since then Candra had become engaged to the High Elf Jeez, though in the span of time leading from that announcement to the present moment that engagement had fallen apart and Jeez was now married to another. Candra kept both rings in a jewelry-box she purchased to hold her impressive collection of such keepsakes.<br>
<br>
Candra's skin prickled as Willius' jade-green gaze moved over her body. She could feel the heat of his regard scanning the curves of her body and the cut of the gown that dressed it. He seemed lost to the sea of creamy flesh immodestly displayed by a daring neckline. &quot;Carryin' on with a married man, Candra? Yer flirtin' with scandal.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Hardly,&quot; she laughed softly into the air between them, her eyes rocking slowly against their lids. &quot;We're just two friends enjoying each others' company at a very public affair. There's nothing salacious about the night's arrangements.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So you say, enchantress. So you say.&quot; Willius' voice trailed off as if he was lost in thought. Candra couldn't but notice how his gaze lingered on her chest, but it was a few before she realized his attentions were not focused on her womanly attributes, but the locket resting against them.<br>
<br>
Candra flinched noticeably as she fought off the instinct to grasp protectively (or perhaps possessively) at the piece. A sense of growing desperation placed an ache in her belly and she struggled with the feeling for the sake of maintaining her cool, calm façade. There were more subtle ways to distract his attention from her latest acquisition.<br>
<br>
Candra brightened her smile and focused her attention on the larger-than-life Willius. Or, more properly, she focused his attention on her. The blood in her veins grew hot and she pulled his eyes to her. To her flesh, her eyes, her hair. Her voice breezed over his subconscious mind. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Am I not beautiful, Willius?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Willius reacted, certainly. She saw admiration, lust, even fascination, bloom in him. His pupils dilated and his neck produced a few beads of sweat. His hands shook just a bit. He licked his gaping lips to wet them and murmured absently, &quot;Most beautiful...&quot;<br>
<br>
Candra grinned at Willius like a cat with a belly full of mouse. &quot;You should go now, darling.&quot; Her voice was soft and sweet, even gentle. The power that rode it, however, was demanding. That power transformed her enticing request into the charm of command. &quot;You're awfully tired and it's so late. Go to your bed now and sleep. When you wake you'll remember only that you had a grand time in my company before taking your leave. You'll forget about my necklace along with any thoughts regarding its design or nature. Understood?&quot;<br>
<br>
Willius seemed transfixed as he replied, &quot;Yes, mistress. I should go,&quot; he leaned forward to place a kiss on her lips and Candra let him. Though she would never admit it, Candra savored the simple joy of being with him and felt the undercurrent of passion long denied building anew. She allowed the kiss to linger for longer than was prudent, but eventually found the will to break their embrace. She was more than a little surprised when Willius hold of her tightened and held her still.<br>
<br>
The barbarian grinned wolfishly at her, &quot;I said 'I should go', not that I would.&quot; He quickly stole another kiss before the enchantress could react. As her small hands pushed and her womanly shape struggled against his muscular form, Willius found it impossible to hold back the loud, bellowing laughter that had been building inside him since the enchantress' charm had faded. He finally set her free as her futile tantrum only made him laugh harder and his belly was aching from the excitement.<br>
<br>
Candra in turn reacted with an anger that brought brilliant color to her face. &quot;How could you?!&quot; the velvet was slipping away from her voice now and revealing cold iron beneath.<br>
<br>
&quot;Easy now, 'chantress. Let's not forget just who should be tha one upset here.&quot; Willius was still laughing as he attempted to arrest the situation. &quot;We agreed that ya would keep yer mind tricks to yerself.&quot;<br>
<br>
There was little to argue about and Candra was fully aware of that fact. The embarrassment for her folly and anger for her failure left her feeling warm and flustered. She took a moment to catch her breath before making a feeble attempt to save face. &quot;You kissed me.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ya let me,&quot; Willius countered.<br>
<br>
&quot;No, I didn't. It wasn't like that.&quot; An obvious lie, but she remained unwilling to live with knowledge of that truth.<br>
<br>
&quot;And ya liked it, I think.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Arrogant bastard!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Candra was losing ground with this argument and she knew it. She'd lost the upper hand and with that control of the situation. She needed time to think and that was the one thing Willius was not willing to give her. With a sigh she turned about and cast her gaze towards the heavens to take in the velvety night sky, the diamonds that twinkled against it and the silver sorcery of the full moon.<br>
<br>
Willius laid a hand on her bare shoulder and she shivered. His hand was rough, but still impossibly gentle. “Tha spirits grow restless in yer wake, Candra.” He turned her about to see her face, search her eyes. “They murmur of dark deeds and even darker sorcery. Tell me, lass, what have ye done?”<br>
<br>
Candra was barely aware of her arms folded over her chest or the tension that was moving through her body. She was uncomfortable under the scrutiny of the shaman’s powerful gaze. His Craft was something she could not fathom, born from a realm she could not access and entities she could neither charm nor control. Talk of spirits made her nervous. “I don’t have time for this prattle, Willius.” She started to leave, but Willius’ grip on her shoulder held her fast and forced her to look at him.<br>
<br>
“Yer a fool if ya think yer alone, Candra. The spirits surround ye, slumbering in yer home, nestling in yer clothes, kissing you through that comb in yer hair. They’re everywhere. Ye can’t see them, but I can. I can hear their cries,” his green eyes darted to the locket resting against her breasts then returned to her eyes, “I can feel their pain.”<br>
<br>
“Enough!” Candra clutched the locket against her chest and shrugged off the barbarian’s touch. “You don’t scare me with all this talk of nonsense, Willius.”<br>
<br>
Intense color crept into the rough edges of Willius' countenance, his ears and cheeks and neck. Candra could feel the heat radiating from his mountainous body. Still he showed remarkable restraint when he spoke. “Yer no <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>mystery</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> ta me, Candra. I see ya for what ya are. Ambitious, lying, conniving. I’ve never once complained, never once thought ta interfere with your schemes, or to turn ya from these strange ways. But there comes a time...”<br>
<br>
Candra had heard enough. Her ego, her fear, her guilt and greed – none could bear the burden of shame that Willius was attempting to evoke. It took only a moment for the enchantress to connect with thoughts, the fiery passion that drove him and snuff it out like some candle whose light was no longer needed. He stood before her, mesmerized and impotent. A slick of drool ran from the corner of his mouth.<br>
<br>
“Remember nothing, Willius.” She commanded and he had no choice but to obey. The barbarian blinked as his memories fled and the enchantress along with them. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=candraverbena>Candra Verbena</A> at: 5/21/03 7:52:10 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=99.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=99.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.elvenelite.com/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=99.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.threadControl?topicID=99.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=99.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=99.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="elvenelitefrm6">Membership